<TEXT>
indiana republicans dispirited and in 
disarray after losing the governors office for the first time in 
two decades believe indianapolis mayor william h hudnut could 
help lead a party revival 
the fourterm mayor often credited with engineering the 
revitalization of indianas largest city is running for secretary 
of state the job pays almost 29000 less than the mayors office 
and has only a fraction of the responsibility 
but the political payoff could be significant republicans 
believe if hudnut defeats incumbent democrat joseph h hogsett and 
helps the gop gain control of the state legislature for the 
important redistricting session of 1991 
a hudnut victory this year also could put the mayor in line to 
challenge gov evan bayh in 1992 many believe the firstterm 
democratic governor used the secretary of states race in 1986 as a 
springboard for his gubernatorial campaign two years later 
i think the party that wins this year particularly in terms 
of the legislative races will control the political landscape for 
the rest of this decade said hudnut 57 
party leaders believe hudnut who entered the race in early 
february already has helped the partys fundraising boosted 
morale and helped recruit legislative candidates 
the hudnut candidacy has added a spirit of enthusiasm across 
the board said state gop chairman keith luse 
that enthusiasm was missing after bayh defeated lt gov john m 
mutz in 1988 bringing an end to 20 years of gop rule at the 
statehouse republicans elected and then rejected one state 
chairman other candidates for secretary of state failed to fire up 
the troops and appointed sen dan coats spent thousands of dollars 
trying to boost his name recognition to a level hudnut already 
enjoys upon entering statewide politics 
i think the republican party since 1988 was wallowing around a 
little bit and sort of licking its wounds and was kind of 
dispirited said hudnut a former presbyterian minister 
one of the strengths i hope i bring to this effort is the 
ability to galvanize the troops to make them feel as though what 
theyre doing is important to make them feel as though 1988 is 
behind us and were moving ahead now 
that the party turned to hudnut is ironic in light of his past 
relationship with the gop hierarchy which quashed a drafthudnut 
movement before the 1988 governors race 
hudnut maintains hes long been popular with the partys rank 
and file a view confirmed by luse who said party functions have 
been filled to capacity since the mayor entered the secretary of 
states race 
that popularity could help the entire ticket and more 
important hudnut gives the party a charismatic leader who could 
turn the 1990 election into a referendum on bayhs administration 
and pose a direct threat to bayhs reelection plans some leaders 
believe 
hudnut says you never say never when asked if he wants 
someday to run for governor he said he cant afford to look ahead 
to 1992 because he considers himself an underdog against a 
wellfinanced hogsett campaign 
hogsett a 33yearold attorney who managed bayhs two statewide 
campaigns also claims hes the underdog because hudnut begins the 
race with a sizeable name recognition advantage appointed 
secretary of state when bayh became governor hogsett has never 
before run for office 
although the two candidates wont be formally nominated until 
their parties state conventions in june hudnut and hogsett 
already are touring the state regularly to take swipes at each 
other 
hogsett takes the mayor to task for 19 tax increases and 
creation of eight new taxes during his tenure hudnut says hogsett 
shows a lack of experience a lack of governmental competence 
in leveling charges about financial matters the mayor claims his 
opponent doesnt understand 
hudnut also has been on the defensive in recent weeks trying to 
explain why he visited a psychic for marital counseling before he 
and his second wife were divorced in 1988 
hudnut calls the matter personal and says he doesnt see any 
conflict between his religious training and the psychics beliefs 
in astrology and reincarnation 
