meetings in favor of a 13member council and fulltime city manager 
residents of the city which calls itself americas hometown 
voted 4019 to 3354 saturday to keep the current form of 
government in which more than 100 town meeting representatives 
govern a board of five selectmen 
proponents and opponents of the measure agree however that 
some governmental changes might be necessary in the town where the 
mayflower landed 
