charges of inefficiency baloney 
ive never seen an issue come before the town that couldnt be 
acted on quickly enough he said 
but malaguti agreed a town administrator might be needed 
although he said the basic town meeting format should remain 
unchanged 
while plymouths present system of government can be traced back 
to the first town meetings held in 1636 it has been updated 
through the years 
rather than having town meetings in which all citizens could 
show up to vote eight town representatives are elected in 
nonpartisan races in each of 13 precincts 
the 104person body meets at least annually to approve major 
decisions proposed by five selectmen who are elected by voters 
selectmen gather biweekly to oversee city operations 
