approved his sons involvement in the maritime authority in 1988 
actual conflicts of interest are felonies and activities which 
give the appearance of such conflicts are prohibited by a 
presidential executive order and by state department rules 
one federal regulation bars an employee from having a direct 
or indirect financial interest that conflicts substantially or 
appears to conflict substantially with the employees government 
duties or responsibilities 
another says an employee cannot engage in directly or 
indirectly a financial transaction as a result of or primarily 
relying on information obtained through government employment 
fred zeder said none of these rules applied to his involvement 
with island development i understand that state department 
procedures may have changed somewhat since 1987 he added 
a native of new jersey who later moved to dallas zeder is a 
wealthy businessman and one of bushs closest friends they went 
fishing together earlier this month in florida 
zeder raised funds for bush during his presidential campaign 
and he and secretary of state james baker iii were the highestpaid 
advisers in bushs presidential transition office bush nominated 
zeder last year to head opic a government agency that promotes 
economic development abroad 
his name did not appear on island developments original 1986 
incorporation papers he concealed his initial involvement by 
having his attorneys and his business partner named as directors 
however zeders wife martha zeder and his lawyers told the 
associated press that zeder formed the company 
zeder hired the law firm to set up the foundation and i 
happened to be assigned to the case said lawyer alan b burdick 
who signed the charter of incorporation 
asked why he did not have the lawyers list him on the 
incorporation papers zeder said he formed it as an inoperative 
shelf corporation in case he wanted to do business after 
leaving the state department 
as ambassador zeder negotiated compacts to establish new 
political relationships with the us trust territory that is now 
palau the republic of the marshall islands the federated states 
of micronesia and the commonwealth of the northern marianas 
he also dealt with development in 1986 he signed agreements 
for a total of 30 million in us economic assistance to 
micronesia and the marshalls under two investment development 
funds the funds give grants and loans to encourage joint ventures 
and private enterprise in the regions 
incorporation papers for zeders business say it was established 
to solicit participation and cooperation in the economic 
development plans of various nations territories and other 
jurisdictions in the pacific islands 
in the interview zeder said the company obtained a few business 
clients but did not make a substantial amount of money he said 
123334 he received from the company after leaving the state 
