<TEXT>
a new species of termite a tiny 
blackwinged pest that swarms in summer and hunts for dead wood 
has been discovered in this gulf coast town 
rudy scheffrahn a termite expert with the university of 
floridas institute of food and agricultural sciences calls it 
the biggest termite find in the last 40 years 
the recently found termite which is less than an eighthinch 
long is called amitermes floridensis the relatively harmless 
creature is half the size and onefifth the weight of its more 
robust florida cousins and its content to gnaw on dead tree 
branches rather than 2by4s 
scheffrahn doesnt know yet whether amitermes floridensis is a 
native st petersburg resident or was brought from out of state 
some 16 termite species are in florida and 44 throughout the 
united states 
anytime you find a new species its exciting because weve 
come to believe there isnt anything new in the world scheffrahn 
said 
