housing and urban development now acknowledge they misinterpreted a 
1987 change in federal law and that the certificates can be used 
outside the community in which they are issued 
the opportunity for finding decent housing is going to be 
expanded greatly said robert m sabel a rhode island legal 
services lawyer who represented ms smith 
in rhode island 4417 families use the certificates for 
housing families must earn less than half the average local annual 
income and must contribute 30 percent of their income for rent 
