her nursing studies and caring for her children the oldest of whom 
is 10 
hud officials admitted they were wrong in january and later 
us district judge ronald r lagueux approved a settlement the 
providence journal reported monday 
the 1987 law said a certificate issued in a metropolitan area 
can be used anywhere within it so poor people arent forced to 
congregate in one area but hud officials originally interpreted 
that to mean the certificate must be used in the city where it was 
issued 
the agency now has ruled that a certificate is good for an area 
that includes a city and all the surrounding communities with 
strong economic and social ties to it for providence that 
includes all of rhode island as well as eight communities in 
massachusetts 
hud spokesman bill glavin said the federal agency soon would 
tell all housing authorities of the change 
