investment corporation opic one of its few profitmaking 
agencies for the year that ended last september the corporation 
turned over 122 million to the treasury it earned the money 
largely by insuring americans against hostile acts to their 
property in other countries 
for democracys sake weve got to do all we can to help this 
transition take place bush told the annual meeting of the us 
chamber of commerce 
private us investors are expected to supply the remaining 150 
million the government corporation will insurethem against having 
their money blocked or confiscated and against war and violence in 
the countries where the fund will be active 
james v hall the corporations spokesman said the fund should 
