<TEXT>
west german leaders attempted monday 
to overcome kremlin opposition to a united germany belonging to 
nato as preparations got under way for historic unification talks 
experts from the two germanys and the four victorious world war 
ii powers held closeddoor procedural talks in east berlin to 
prepare for the formal twoplusfour negotiations at the 
foreign ministers level in bonn 
after six hours of talks they issued a joint statement saying 
that polands borders would be the first item discussed when the 
foreign ministers from the six nations hold their first formal 
talks on may 5 in bonn 
poland is demanding guarantees that a united germany will not 
seek to reclaim former german lands ceded to poland after world war 
ii 
in a meeting monday west german foreign minister hansdietrich 
genscher assured victor karpov the soviet deputy foreign minister 
that bonn would not overlook moscows justified security 
interests 
genscher told the soviet official that german unification would 
represent the solution of a serious european problem the 
division of europe and not the creation of a new one 
in an effort to make some headway before saturdays 
twoplusfour talks the west german government announced that 
genscher would hold separate meetings friday with soviet foreign 
minister eduard a shevardnadze and us secretary of state james 
a baker iii 
baker will also meet friday with west german chancellor helmut 
kohl said west german government spokesman dieter vogel 
kohl indicated that west germany was prepared to offer economic 
and other incentives to the soviet union to overcome reservations 
about german unification within nato 
kohl in a statement read by vogel said he is certain that we 
will come to a reasonable agreement also with the soviet union 
on the matter of a united germanys strategic allegiances 
kohl added that west germany is ready for comprehensive 
cooperation with the soviet union in the areas of economy 
technological exchanges athletic meetings and cooperation in 
security questions 
kohls statement did not elaborate west germany is the soviet 
unions largest trading partner in the west 
in bonn east and west german negotiators tried to wrap up their 
own talks on merging the economies of the two countries by july 2 
east germany is pressing west germany to sweeten its proposed 
terms for economic union but the west germans have indicated their 
unwillingness to make further concessions 
despite the differences vogel told reporters the two germanys 
still intend to forge a basic economic agreement by friday 
on saturday foreign ministers from east and west germany and 
the soviet union france and britain as well as baker are to meet 
in bonn to try to iron out the thorny strategic problems raised by 
german unification 
mikhail s gorbachev reiterated the soviet unions opposition to 
a united germanys membership in nato during a meeting sunday in 
moscow with east german prime minister lothar de maiziere 
the soviet union is concerned that a unified germany within nato 
would upset the current european balance of power to moscows 
disadvantage 
shevardnadze has signaled that moscow was prepared to drop its 
demand for a neutral unified germany he said the soviet union is 
open to proposals for new european security structures including a 
proposal that a united germany belong to both nato and the warsaw 
pact 
west germany and its nato allies have insisted that a united 
germany must remain in the western alliance 
de maizere was quoted in the east german communist party 
newspaper neues deutschland on monday as saying east germany should 
act as a mediator between the soviet union and the west on german 
unification 
east germany has said it is willing to go along with temporary 
nato membership if the alliance undergoes fundamental changes 
reflecting the eastwest thaw by emphasizing political and economic 
issues over its military role 
