reform package typical of the states in the region since the early 
1980s 
kentucky recently overhauled its entire school system after the 
state supreme court ruled it unconstitutional because of variances 
in districttodistrict spending louisiana arkansas mississippi 
and tennessee have passed reforms to address entrenched delta 
realities 
according to the last census for example dropout rates in the 
region averaged 25 percent compared with 20 percent nationally 
and ran more than 40 percent in seven delta counties 
the census also found that 45 percent of delta residents older 
than 25 and six of 10 blacks in that group never finished high 
school 
