<TEXT>
for more than a year s epatha merkerson built 
her life and career around the piano lesson her loyalty has 
paid off 
the actress turned down work that interfered with the plays 
offandon travels from chicago to san diego to washington to los 
angeles and now new york she accepted shortterm job assignments 
to fill in the employment gaps a small movie role here a guest 
spot on television there 
its been that important merkerson says now it always 
was a dream of mine to act but i dont think i could ever have 
dreamed of this if any kid ever wants to do anything i am living 
proof that you can dream of something and have it come true 
three days before the piano lesson opened on broadway last 
month it won the pulitzer prize for playwright august wilson 
reviewers not only cheered the play but singled out merkerson for 
her portrayal of berniece a strong woman determined to keep a 
family heirloom an old upright piano from being sold 
the play part of wilsons decadebydecade chronicle of the 
black experience in america focuses on a battle between brother 
and sister the brother played by charles s dutton is determined 
to sell the piano to buy the land their ancestors worked on as 
slaves the sister wants to keep it as a reminder of their painful 
past 
i know berniece says the exuberant merkerson the opposite 
of the reserved uptight woman she plays what we have in common 
is that i am a collector too but on a small scale of black 
history i like to keep things and so does berniece i collect 
golliwogs black memorabilia 
merkerson was hired for the piano lesson without an 
audition solely on the strength of a recommendation from casting 
directors meg simon and fran kumin but she had a rapport with both 
wilson and director lloyd richards 
lloyd lets the actor create and as long as you are within the 
concept of the play that we have all been discussing and reading 
you are fine she says he trusts the people that he hires 
during the long tour wilson refined the play even changing the 
ending to have more of a resolution in the fight over that piano 
in the year and three months that ive been on the road with 
the play certain things changed every time we did it and even 
changed up until the rehearsal here for broadway merkerson says 
so its been an ongoing process and were still finding new 
things which is marvelous its still very fresh for us even 
though some people in the cast have been doing it for two years 
merkersons family from michigan wasnt in show business 
although they were very theatrical everybody played an instrument 
sang or danced 
but im the only one who actually pursued it says 
merkerson born in saginaw but raised in detroit and they sort 
