the rainbow is enuf 
the women i worked with in the for colored girls company 
gave me the most valuable advice she says they knew i was 
green and they said look no one knows you but us and your 
mother you make sure you do as much good work as you can get your 
name out there because then people will know you do good work and 
are reliable 
merkersons other work in new york includes replacing lonette 
mckee in lady day at emersons bar and grill three ways 
home and moms the story of moms mabley starring clarice 
taylor 
i recall going into an audition for a big name director of a 
film and he asked me who i studied with merkerson says i 
started naming the people i had worked with like adolph caesar 
barbara montgomery and mary alice 
my most valuable lessons have come from those actors i have 
worked with i really are the people who have 
helped me they have taught me by watching me work and my being 
able to work alongside them they are truly my teachers 
one constant throughout her career has been the actress refusal 
to change her name ffeel like those or the stage 
epatha was the name given me at birth says merkerson i 
was named for a woman who was very influential in keeping my dad in 
school 
the s stands for sharon but no one in my family calls me 
that she adds 
people have told me that my name was very difficult and that i 
should change it she says but i figure once you learn it you 
wont forget it only recently did i learn there was some meaning 
