<TEXT>
the gods must be crazy entranced world audiences with its 
simple comedic tale of an african nomad who finds a cocacola 
bottle and transforms it into an icon 
there was a slapstick romantic subplot as well but the films 
great appeal stemmed from the character of the smiling openfaced 
actor with the impossible name of nxau 
those who embraced the film will naturally approach the gods 
must be crazy ii with misgivings sequels never equal the 
original they say the godfather ii was a rare exception 
the gods ii cant possibly approach the joy of discovering 
the delightful nxau but the new film is a creditable attempt 
combining another amusing malefemale subplot with the central 
story about nxaus search for his lost children 
jamie uys a veteran south african filmmaker composes his films 
like silent comedies jammed with sight gags they are almost 
playable without dialogue uys even uses the silentmovie technique 
of speeding up the action by undercranking the camera to 
punctuate the comedy 
his script presents three parallel and sometimes intersecting 
plots 
1 two young children of nxau accidentally land in the truck 
of some poachers racing across the desert with a cargo of elephant 
tusks the distraught father finds the trail and races after them 
day and night 
2 a new york lawyer lena farugia attends a conference in 
southern africa she takes a sightseeing flight in a tiny plane 
which crashes in the wildernesses a research zoologist hans 
strydom agrees to lead her back to civilization their journey 
encountering a series of mishaps 
3 a unita scout treasure tshabalala and a cuban soldier 
erick bowen encounter each other in the wild and wage comical 
oneonone warfare 
the stories dont always mesh neatly and some of the comedy 
bits prove tedious such as the heroines climbing up and down a 
tower to pump water but there are a few bellylaughs and nxau 
remains a captivating figure the two youngsters eiros and nadies 
are absolute wonders 
some will argue that uys could have extracted lessons in the 
senselessness of war the corruption of civilization the 
dangers to wildlife but he is an entertainer not a preacher and 
for that we can be grateful 
produced by boet troskie and released by columbia pictures 
the gods must be crazy ii is rated pg but it seems acceptable 
for all audiences running time 97 minutes 
</TEXT>
