reported cases of elder abuse rose 12 percent in 
massachusetts last year reflecting a steady increase over five 
years a state official said 
according to the study reports of elder abuse and neglect 
increased to 3094 for the year ended june 30 1989 compared to 
2769 cases the previous year 
reported cases in the 1984 fiscal year totaled only 1529 so 
the latest statistics represent an increase of 102 percent within 
six years 
for every report of abuse or neglect we receive we know that 
there are many others who suffer in silence said elder affairs 
