millions of americans have benefited from the 
social security act approved by congress in 1935 but the social 
security administration says that by the year 2048 money for the 
future may be depleted if congress continues to borrow against the 
fund 
there is strong evidence that social security might radically 
change by the time todays baby boomers reach retirement age 
because of the uncertainty about the future of social security and 
the extent to which corporations will continue to contribute to 
retirement funds for employees my advice to all consumers is to 
begin planning now for retirement 
americans are almost evenly split on the issue of whether the 
social security system will be able to pay them retirement 
benefits reponding to an employee benefit research institute and 
gallup survey 47 percent of those surveyed said they would 
probably not get a penny from the social security fund while 49 
