concern among clients of financial planners most clients dont 
begin retirement planning until they are 35 to 44 years old 10 
years later than most planners recommend 
there are many reasons why all consumers should begin planning 
today for retirement increased longevity rates mean we will have 
longer retirements than previous generations planning for 
longterm care and medical expenses which are rising annually at 
a rate of 20 percent to 30 percent should also be a key concern 
further because most people want to maintain the same standard of 
living they enjoyed while working money thats put away for 
retirement must account for inflation which typically increases 
45 percent annually 
i advise all consumers to take these small steps now 
participate in a companysponsored savings program most of 
which earn taxdeferred interest until retirement if you are 
selfemployed set up a keogh plan 
save at least 10 percent of income preferably 15 percent to 
20 percent 
invest in an individual retirement account or ira one of the 
few taxdeferred saving programs remaining since the enactment of 
the tax reform act 
consider taxsheltered annuities if you work for a religious 
charitable or educational organization or state university or 
public school system you may be eligible to participate in a 
taxsheltered annuity plan 
consider taxexempt or taxdeferred investments such as 
municipal bonds or singlepremium or flexiblepremium deferred 
annuities 
consider diversifying your portfolio to include stocks or real 
estate if you feel comfortable with these growth investments 
