of virginia vegetable growers will be fascinated by the kitchen 
garden stretching 1000 feet along the sunny southern slope and 
containing more than 250 varieties including english peas 
jeffersons favorite a virginian of his times jefferson had 
slaves to help him but he was deeply troubled by the question and 
was one of the first americans to propose a plan of abolition 
through correspondence and accounts of others the garden book 
admirably annotated by edwin morris betts a biology professor at 
