would require more than 300000 floridians to prove theyre not 
hazardous drivers beginning in 1991 
while ms lewis contends the measure would keep dangerous 
drivers off the road critics say the bill is discriminatory that 
argument helped kill her bill in committee last year 
in 1986 a similar bill proposed by sen jack gordon failed when 
legislators were swamped by mail from constituents opposing the 
idea 
ms lewis bill has cleared the house committee on highway 
safety and she is optimistic the measure will pass the legislature 
this year 
the people of florida favor testing elderly drivers even 
before they reach 80 lewis said the bill is such a minimal 
step toward getting unsafe drivers off our roads i think we should 
be retesting drivers starting at age 60 and im 60 
some legislators say the bill discriminates against a specific 
age group and makes no provision for transportation for those no 
longer able to drive 
