<TEXT>
digital computer corp and apple computer inc 
will announce products on tuesday that allow digital and apple 
computers to connect easily the first fruit of a 2yearold 
alliance between the companies 
through the software apple macintosh personal computers will be 
able to share computer files with digital machines to send 
messages to digital computers and to use printers hooked up to a 
digital network among other things said john rose who heads 
digitals personal computer division 
theyre all done with the macintosh friendly user interface 
said rose referring to the onscreen graphics display that makes 
the macintosh easy to use by replacing typed commands with pictures 
several outside suppliers provide software to connect apple and 
digital computers but rose said none is as comprehensive as the 
digitalapple system 
digital computers usually are connected in a network or to a 
mainframe computer while the macintosh a desktop computer 
usually is a standalone machine the software will allow companies 
using both types of machines to link them in a network 
there is a substantial audience out there for the products 
rose said 
laura conigliaro an analyst at prudentialbache securities 
inc agreed that the market for the products could be 
considerable she said there are many companies that rely on both 
digital and apple computers 
she said the products are important for apple because it needs a 
credible server or a computer that acts as the central file 
repository in a network of computers while digital needs a desktop 
computer that has wide acceptance 
it has some positive marketability for both companies she 
said 
digital based in maynard mass and apple based in cupertino 
calif announced their intention to develop the products in 
january 1988 
in the past two years digital the secondlargest computer 
company after international business machines corp has released 
products that allow ibm computers to be linked with digital 
machines 
ms conigliaro said the delay in releasing the appledigital 
products probably is due to the kind of things that go on when 
companies are big and bureaucracy is the modus operandi 
linking computers from various makers is becoming increasingly 
popular as the computer industry moves from proprietary or 
companyspecific computers and software to machines and software 
that adhere to industrywide standards 
companies increasingly want all their computers to be able to 
communicate with each other and to share files analysts say 
rose said additional products to further link apple and digital 
computers will be announced in the future 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

