<TEXT>
a trade association of bond dealers has 
announced plans for a joint venture to supply prices 24 hours a 
day responding to a longstanding government request for improved 
distribution of market information 
among those eligible to participate in the joint venture are 44 
primary dealers and seven interbroker dealers said the public 
securities association 
within 60 days of formation the venture could begin to 
disseminate price information said psa general counsel fran 
bermanzohn 
primary dealers buy and sell government bonds and participate in 
treasury auctions interbroker dealers execute trades for 
securities firms but not for the general public 
the move was overwhelmingly approved by the psas primary 
dealers committee last friday at a meeting in white sulphur 
springs va 
the jointventure would negotiate to sell the data to several 
electronic information systems currently brokers get bond quotes 
from financial data services such as telerate inc and reuters 
holdings plc among others 
the government has been pressuring brokers to make price 
information more widely available to the public the general 
accounting office made the recommendation several years ago 
the joint venture is being done in large measure in response 
to a regulatory mandate bermanzohn said many dealers take the 
position that the price information is already out there 
the prices available from the venture would be real time 
quotes which show the last sale price as trades are executed 
between dealers 
the group decided that the best prices would be from the 
industry as a whole as opposed to any group forming together to 
provide a number said thomas pura who chairs the psas 
goverment and federal agency division 
many providers of bond prices have exclusive arrangements with 
interbroker dealers telerate for example has a multiple year 
contract with the cantor fitzgerald brokerage to provide exclusive 
quotes on telerate screens 
the associated press has a similar arrangment with bloomberg 
financial markets which in turn is supplied by merrill lynch 
pura noted that while the price information currently available 
is very good the new system will provide even more information 
will they be significantly different no but people feel 
better having broader access to price information pura said 
