analysts estimate the organization of petroleum exporting 
countries currently is producing about 235 million barrels a day 
exceeding the ceiling of 221 million barrels a day the cartel set 
for the first half of the year 
the 13nation cartel accounts for a substantial portion of the 
world oil market and increasingly influences prices in the united 
states where imports now account for about half the nations 
consumption 
the opec meeting was called april 19 by sadek boussena 
algerias oil minister and cartel president because of concern 
about an unusually sharp price slide that pushed prices down to the 
1516 barrel range vs more than 20 earlier in the year the 
meeting is expected to last one or two days 
the gathering officially is of the eightmember monitoring 
committee which only reviews markets and makes recommendations 
but all ministers are expected to attend which means a full 
emergency conference can be called immediately 
but the ministers arent expected to grapple with their official 
quotas and minimum reference price of 18 a barrel until they hold 
their full regular midyear conference on june 25 
boussena is spearheading intensive contacts among opec members 
to reach consensus on voluntary cuts before wednesday the middle 
east economic survey a nicosiabased oil industry newsletter 
reported monday 
a contentious gathering could have a negative impact on oil 
markets 
