robert r davis a member of the commodity 
futures trading commission since 1984 announced he was resigning 
monday to take an executive position with the new york mercantile 
exchange 
an economist davis was nomiated to the fivemember cftc by 
president reagan he said he will join the new york exchange as 
senior vice president for planning and development 
in his letter of resignation to president bush davis called the 
cftc a model of good government that constructively channeled the 
invisible hand of the market and avoided laying on the dead 
hand of excessive regulation 
the cftc which oversees the futures industry has come under 
fire in the wake of a major fraud scandal at the nations two 
largest futures exchanges in chicago 
critics in congress and the administration have suggested 
merging the agency with the rival securities and exchange 
commission or giving the sec control over securitiesrelated 
futures currently overseen by the cftc 
davis who has bachelors masters and doctoral degrees in 
economics from virginia polytechnic institute served as senior 
economist for the joint economic committee of congress before his 
appointment to the cftc 
he also has served as a financial economist to the federal 
deposit insurance corporation and a vice president at the harris 
bank in chicago 
