<TEXT>
change in the way manufacturers and others 
stock their inventories helped head off a recession at the 
beginning of the year federal reserve chairman alan greenspan told 
a group purchasing managers monday 
the obvious question is what went wrong with the recession 
forecasts or more exactly what went right with the economy while 
analysts can never be certain of such things there is at least 
presumptive evidence that a major reason perhaps the key reason 
is the marked change in inventory behavior on the part of 
purchasing managers in manufacturing and elsewhere greenspan 
said 
speaking to the 75th annual conference of the national 
association of purchasing management greenspan said changes in the 
inventory cycle are a factor in driving industrial activity in 
the nation 
the economy began to show prerecession symptoms in the second 
quarter of 1989 greenspan said by autumn the signs pointing to a 
recession were more abundant he said 
the weakness in industrial activity bottomed out around the turn 
of the year greenspan said without spreading to other areas of 
the economy 
most if not all past american recessions have been sparked 
or at least aggravated by large inventory swings he said 
modern delivery methods the use of computers to track inventory 
and predict demand and the availability of goods internationally 
have helped prevent the cycle of overstocking and then cutting 
back greenspan said that cycle which in turn forces suppliers to 
adjust their production schedules has not been evident on the 
industrial scene in recent years he said 
greenspan said there will be other reductions of goods that 
affect the business cycle 
the number of cars and trucks owned by households and businesses 
is adequate now he said and sales are likely to reflect primarily 
replacement needs and slower growth in the drivingage population 
in the housing market the low birth rate of the 1960s and 1970s 
means that the building rate in the 1990s will be lower than in the 
1980s greenspan said 
increased interest rates since the first of the year on home 
mortgages and difficulty in obtaining credit by segments of the 
construction industry have also slowed building but the 
difficulties should diminish considerably over time as they 
secure other financing sources he said 
the volume of imports of merchandise excluding oil has 
declined in recent months greenspan said 
overall these indicators point to somewhere between modest 
and moderate growth in factory output over the coming year 
greenspan said 
</TEXT>
