<TEXT>
the spanishlanguage television network 
telemundo and consumer products giant procter amp gamble are 
launching a halfhour program in which procters products will be 
prominently featured as solutions to a variety of common domestic 
problems the companies said monday 
the show is called hablando and will appear on the telemundo 
network twice a week starting tuesday afternoon 
the telemundo network is one of the nations largest 
spanishlanguage tv networks reaching 36 major markets and an 
estimated 78 percent of the hispanic housholds in the united states 
telemundo productions which is producing the show described 
the program as infotainment or a mixture of education 
information and entertainment 
the show features three actors and guest appearances that 
portray people in a variety of settings including the kitchen and 
the laundry room 
procter amp gamble brands such as luvs diapers scope mouthwash 
and tide laundry detergent are prominently displayed and used 
during various segments of the program in which topics such as 
caring for the baby personal hygiene or cleaning the family wash 
are discussed 
procter amp gamble is also the sole national advertiser on the 
program pitching many of the same products that appear within the 
show in the four minutes of network commercials allowed each half 
hour 
critics of infotainment or infomercials say shows that 
pitch specific products in return for a fee from the manufacturer 
are inappropriate because viewers may mistake them for 
independently produced programs 
but saul p steinberg chairman president and chief executive 
of telemundo group inc defended the arrangement with procter amp 
gamble saying that such associations are common on television in 
spanishspeaking countries 
he said the program provides useful information on local customs 
for people who may have only recently arrived and that it would 
have been a much more expensive undertaking without procter amp 
gambles sponsorship 
viewers will be the judge of the value of the program steinberg 
said saying it will survive for long if its ratings are poor 
nonetheless he added that you can only do so much of this 
and wants a large majority of independent entertainment programming 
on his network 
neil m comber manager of target marketing for cincinnatibased 
procter amp gamble said his company paid a premium of about 5 
percent to 10 percent over the costs of commercials alone for the 
right to have its products used in the program 
he said the company also recently began sponsoring twominute 
informative programs that are being carried on telemundos 
spanishlanguage network rival univision those programs which 
air several times a day on univision are produced in conjunction 
with the spanishlanguage magazine la familia de hoy published by 
whittle communications of knoxville tenn 
