torchmark inc promised to challenge a 
state regulators order that it halt its proxy fight for control of 
american general corp 
tennessee revenue commissioner joe huddleston said monday that 
torchmark violated state law with its attempt to elect five 
nominees to american generals board of directors on wednesday in 
houston where the insurer is based 
the law says no insurance company or holding company can seek to 
control a tennessee company without prior approval of the state 
department of commerce and insurance 
the change in control statutes are a vital part of the 
regulatory framework that has developed for the protection of 
policyholders interests american general chairman and chief 
executive harold s hook said in houston we are gratified that 
the state of tennessee has acted to order torchmark to comply with 
the law 
torchmark issued a statement promising to go to court to 
challenge the ruling 
huddleston said the proxy action required torchmark to provide 
financial and other detailed information on which the state can 
base its approval or rejection of a takeover american general and 
the state argue that the proxy move by torchmark inc of 
birmingham ala amounts to a takeover which requires approval of 
tennessee 
torchmark contended during a twoday hearing last week that its 
actions do not require it to meet the requirements because a 
successful proxy fight would simply put directors on the board 
willing to discuss a takeover 
torchmark officials also wrote gov ned mcwherter on april 13 to 
advise him among other things that we have no plans to move any 
operations out of tennessee 
tennessee is one of 10 states in which american general is 
considered domiciled because of its operations there regulators in 
texas and new york also have questioned the legality of torchmarks 
proxy solicitation missouri california and virginia have approved 
the process 
torchmark turned to the proxy strategy earlier this month after 
american general turned down its takeover bid of 50 a share in 
cash and 50 worth of torchmark stock 
